body:
Comment 6: 
Issues return when I try building my github.com/andlabs/ui/test program on Mac OS X 10.6
darwin/amd64:

github.com/andlabs/ui(__DATA/__data): unexpected reloc for dynamic symbol
NSObservedObjectKey
github.com/andlabs/ui(__DATA/__data): unhandled relocation for NSObservedObjectKey (type
32 rtype 1)

Again, external linking circumvents the issue. This does not happen on 10.8. I have no
idea what this means, and thus no idea what's going on.

go version devel +2c7ba8c04515 Thu May 08 08:35:49 2014 -0700 darwin/amd64

This happens with $CC set to both gcc and clang, with both darwin/amd64 and darwin/386
builds.

Thanks! (Thanks to hyphenated for pointing me here.)
